    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Daily Store Sales Forecasting\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Project 1 of 10** — Time Series Forecasting Portfolio\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook forecasts **daily total sales** for the Rossmann drugstore chain using historical sales data from 1,115 stores across Germany. The dataset comes from the Kaggle **Rossmann Store Sales** competition.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Attribute | Value |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"|-----------|-------|\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| **Project type** | Time Series Forecasting |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| **Target variable** | `Sales` (daily store revenue) |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| **Date column** | `Date` |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| **Frequency** | Daily (`D`) |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| **Seasonal period** | 7 (weekly cycle) |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| **Primary TS library** | MLForecast |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| **Kaggle competition** | `rossmann-store-sales` |\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"By completing this notebook you will learn how to:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Download and merge a **multi-file retail dataset** (train + store metadata)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Handle **closed-store days** (zero sales when `Open=0`) and decide whether to include them\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Aggregate store-level data to **total daily chain-wide sales** for a clear signal\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Explore **day-of-week effects**, promotion impact, and holiday patterns in daily data\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. Engineer features appropriate for daily frequency: lags at 1, 7, 14, 28 days\\n\",\n",
    "    \"6. Build naive and seasonal-naive (7-day) baselines\\n\",\n",
    "    \"7. Benchmark regressors via LazyPredict on lag-feature tabular view\\n\",\n",
    "    \"8. Run FLAML AutoML with a time budget\\n\",\n",
    "    \"9. Train MLForecast models (LightGBM, XGBoost) with built-in lag/rolling features\\n\",\n",
    "    \"10. Evaluate with MAE, RMSE, MAPE and compare all approaches\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Problem Statement\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Given ~840 days of daily sales records across 1,115 Rossmann drugstores in Germany, **forecast total daily sales for the next 14 days**.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Rossmann stores vary by type, assortment, competition distance, and promotional activity. We aggregate to chain-wide totals for a cleaner univariate signal, then discuss panel-level extensions.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Why This Project Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Inventory management**: Daily sales forecasts drive replenishment decisions for 1,115+ stores, each with unique demand patterns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Staff scheduling**: Accurate daily forecasts directly determine how many employees to schedule per shift.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Promotional planning**: Rossmann runs frequent promotions — understanding their daily lift is critical for ROI measurement.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Holiday preparedness**: German state holidays and school holidays create store-level demand spikes that require advance planning.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The competition provides two key CSV files:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| File | Rows | Description |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"|------|------|-------------|\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| `train.csv` | ~1.02 M | Daily sales: `Store`, `DayOfWeek`, `Date`, `Sales`, `Customers`, `Open`, `Promo`, `StateHoliday`, `SchoolHoliday` |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| `store.csv` | 1,115 | Store metadata: `Store`, `StoreType` (a-d), `Assortment` (a-c), `CompetitionDistance`, `Promo2`, etc. |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Key columns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **`Sales`** — target; daily revenue (integer), 0 when store is closed\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **`Open`** — 1 if store was open, 0 if closed\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **`Promo`** — 1 if store ran a promotion that day\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **`StateHoliday`** — `0` (none), `a` (public), `b` (Easter), `c` (Christmas)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **`StoreType`** — `a`, `b`, `c`, `d` (different store formats)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **`Assortment`** — `a` (basic), `b` (extra), `c` (extended) product range\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **`CompetitionDistance`** — distance in meters to nearest competitor\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source & License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Kaggle competition**: [Rossmann Store Sales](https://www.kaggle.com/competitions/rossmann-store-sales)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **License**: Competition-specific (Kaggle Competition Rules)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Provider**: Rossmann (via Kaggle)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Usage**: Educational purposes only\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Environment Setup\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"def _install(pkg):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"kagglehub\\\", \\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"plotly\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"scikit-learn\\\", \\\"lazypredict\\\", \\\"flaml\\\", \\\"mlforecast\\\", \\\"lightgbm\\\", \\\"xgboost\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"statsmodels\\\", \\\"scipy\\\", \\\"window-ops\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        __import__(pkg.replace(\\\"-\\\", \\\"_\\\"))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        _install(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"All packages ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Imports\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import warnings, os, pathlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import plotly.express as px\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import plotly.graph_objects as go\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error, mean_squared_error\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.linear_model import Ridge\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from lazypredict.Supervised import LazyRegressor\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from flaml import AutoML\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from mlforecast import MLForecast\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from mlforecast.target_transforms import Differences\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import lightgbm as lgb\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import xgboost as xgb\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from statsmodels.tsa.seasonal import seasonal_decompose\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from statsmodels.graphics.tsaplots import plot_acf, plot_pacf\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scipy import stats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pd.set_option(\\\"display.max_columns\\\", 60)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.rcParams[\\\"figure.figsize\\\"] = (14, 5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"All imports successful.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Configuration & Constants\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"PROJECT_NAME = \\\"Daily Store Sales Forecasting\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"KAGGLE_SLUG  = \\\"rossmann-store-sales\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"TARGET  = \\\"Sales\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"DATE    = \\\"Date\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"FREQ    = \\\"D\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SEASON_LENGTH    = 7       # weekly cycle for daily data\\n\",\n",
    "    \"FORECAST_HORIZON = 14     # 14-day forecast\\n\",\n",
    "    \"TEST_SIZE        = FORECAST_HORIZON\\n\",\n",
    "    \"VAL_SIZE         = FORECAST_HORIZON\\n\",\n",
    "    \"RANDOM_STATE     = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"FLAML_BUDGET     = 120    # seconds\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Project : {PROJECT_NAME}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Target  : {TARGET}  |  Freq: {FREQ}  |  Season: {SEASON_LENGTH}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Horizon : {FORECAST_HORIZON} days\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Kaggle Credential Check\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Before downloading, we verify that Kaggle credentials are available. The notebook expects `KAGGLE_API_TOKEN` (or `KAGGLE_USERNAME` + `KAGGLE_KEY`) in system environment variables, or a `kaggle.json` file in `~/.kaggle/`.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"kaggle_ok = False\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if os.environ.get(\\\"KAGGLE_USERNAME\\\") or os.environ.get(\\\"KAGGLE_KEY\\\") or os.environ.get(\\\"KAGGLE_API_TOKEN\\\"):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(\\\"Kaggle credentials found via environment variables.\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    kaggle_ok = True\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"kaggle_json = pathlib.Path.home() / \\\".kaggle\\\" / \\\"kaggle.json\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if kaggle_json.exists():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Kaggle credentials found at {kaggle_json}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    kaggle_ok = True\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if not kaggle_ok:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    raise RuntimeError(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"No Kaggle credentials found!\\\\n\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"Set KAGGLE_API_TOKEN env var, or place kaggle.json in ~/.kaggle/\\\\n\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"See: https://www.kaggle.com/settings -> Create New Token\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    )\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Ready to download.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Download & Loading\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We download the Rossmann Store Sales competition data via `kagglehub`. The download is idempotent — re-running skips if files already exist locally.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import kagglehub\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    data_path = pathlib.Path(kagglehub.competition_download(KAGGLE_SLUG))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"Downloaded to: {data_path}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"kagglehub download failed: {e}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(\\\"Falling back to kaggle CLI...\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    os.makedirs(\\\"data\\\", exist_ok=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ret = os.system(f\\\"kaggle competitions download -c {KAGGLE_SLUG} -p data/ --unzip\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if ret != 0:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        raise RuntimeError(\\\"Both kagglehub and kaggle CLI failed. Check credentials and competition rules acceptance.\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    data_path = pathlib.Path(\\\"data\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"csv_files = sorted(data_path.rglob(\\\"*.csv\\\"))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for f in csv_files:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"  {f.name:35s}  {f.stat().st_size / 1e6:7.2f} MB\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"assert len(csv_files) > 0, \\\"No CSV files found after download!\\\"\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"### Load and merge CSVs\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"def _find(name):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    matches = [f for f in csv_files if name in f.name.lower()]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    assert matches, f\\\"File matching '{name}' not found in {[f.name for f in csv_files]}\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return matches[0]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"train_raw = pd.read_csv(_find(\\\"train\\\"), parse_dates=[\\\"Date\\\"], low_memory=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"store_info = pd.read_csv(_find(\\\"store\\\"))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"train_raw  : {train_raw.shape}  -- {train_raw['Date'].min().date()} to {train_raw['Date'].max().date()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"store_info : {store_info.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"train_raw.head()\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Validation Checks\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=\\\" * 60)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"DATA VALIDATION REPORT\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=\\\" * 60)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"assert \\\"Sales\\\" in train_raw.columns, \\\"Missing 'Sales' column!\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"assert \\\"Date\\\" in train_raw.columns, \\\"Missing 'Date' column!\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\n[train.csv]\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  Shape            : {train_raw.shape[0]:,} rows x {train_raw.shape[1]} cols\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  Date range       : {train_raw['Date'].min().date()} to {train_raw['Date'].max().date()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  Unique stores    : {train_raw['Store'].nunique()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  Missing Sales    : {train_raw['Sales'].isna().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  Zero-sales rows  : {(train_raw['Sales'] == 0).sum()} ({(train_raw['Sales']==0).mean()*100:.1f}%)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  Closed-store rows: {(train_raw['Open'] == 0).sum()} ({(train_raw['Open']==0).mean()*100:.1f}%)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  Promo days       : {train_raw['Promo'].sum()} ({train_raw['Promo'].mean()*100:.1f}%)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  Duplicate rows   : {train_raw.duplicated().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\n[store.csv]\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  StoreType dist   : {store_info['StoreType'].value_counts().to_dict()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  Assortment dist  : {store_info['Assortment'].value_counts().to_dict()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  CompetitionDist NaN: {store_info['CompetitionDistance'].isna().sum()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\nValidation complete.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Data Cleaning / Preprocessing\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We filter to **open stores only** (closed days have Sales=0 and provide no demand signal), then aggregate to total daily chain-wide sales.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Filter to open stores only\\n\",\n",
    "    \"train_open = train_raw[train_raw[\\\"Open\\\"] == 1].copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"After filtering to Open=1: {len(train_open):,} rows (dropped {len(train_raw)-len(train_open):,} closed-store days)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Merge with store metadata\\n\",\n",
    "    \"train_merged = train_open.merge(store_info, on=\\\"Store\\\", how=\\\"left\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Aggregate to daily total sales\\n\",\n",
    "    \"daily = (\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    train_merged\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    .groupby(\\\"Date\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    .agg(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        Sales=(\\\"Sales\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        Customers=(\\\"Customers\\\", \\\"sum\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        Stores_Open=(\\\"Store\\\", \\\"nunique\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        Promo_Pct=(\\\"Promo\\\", \\\"mean\\\"),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    )\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    .reset_index()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    .sort_values(\\\"Date\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    .reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Add day-of-week\\n\",\n",
    "    \"daily[\\\"DayOfWeek\\\"] = daily[\\\"Date\\\"].dt.dayofweek  # 0=Mon, 6=Sun\\n\",\n",
    "    \"daily[\\\"DayName\\\"] = daily[\\\"Date\\\"].dt.day_name()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nAggregated daily series: {len(daily)} days\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Date range: {daily['Date'].min().date()} to {daily['Date'].max().date()}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"daily.head()\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Exploratory Data Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We explore the temporal structure — trend, weekly seasonality, promotion effects, and day-of-week patterns.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Full time-series plot\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig = go.Figure()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=daily[\\\"Date\\\"], y=daily[\\\"Sales\\\"], name=\\\"Total Daily Sales\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                         line=dict(color=\\\"blue\\\", width=1)))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=daily[\\\"Date\\\"], y=daily[\\\"Sales\\\"].rolling(7).mean(),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                         name=\\\"7-day MA\\\", line=dict(color=\\\"red\\\", width=2)))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.update_layout(title=\\\"Rossmann — Total Daily Sales (All Stores)\\\", template=\\\"plotly_white\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                  xaxis_title=\\\"Date\\\", yaxis_title=\\\"Total Daily Sales\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.show()\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Day-of-week effect\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig = px.box(daily, x=\\\"DayName\\\", y=\\\"Sales\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"             category_orders={\\\"DayName\\\": [\\\"Monday\\\",\\\"Tuesday\\\",\\\"Wednesday\\\",\\\"Thursday\\\",\\\"Friday\\\",\\\"Saturday\\\",\\\"Sunday\\\"]},\\n\",\n",
    "    \"             title=\\\"Sales Distribution by Day of Week\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.update_layout(template=\\\"plotly_white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.show()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Mean daily sales by day of week:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(daily.groupby(\\\"DayName\\\")[\\\"Sales\\\"].mean().reindex(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    [\\\"Monday\\\",\\\"Tuesday\\\",\\\"Wednesday\\\",\\\"Thursday\\\",\\\"Friday\\\",\\\"Saturday\\\",\\\"Sunday\\\"]).to_string())\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Monthly seasonality\\n\",\n",
    "    \"daily[\\\"Month\\\"] = daily[\\\"Date\\\"].dt.month\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig = px.box(daily, x=\\\"Month\\\", y=\\\"Sales\\\", title=\\\"Sales Distribution by Month\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.update_layout(template=\\\"plotly_white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.show()\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Seasonal decomposition\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ts = daily.set_index(\\\"Date\\\")[\\\"Sales\\\"].asfreq(\\\"D\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ts = ts.interpolate() if ts.isna().any() else ts\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"decomp = seasonal_decompose(ts, model=\\\"additive\\\", period=SEASON_LENGTH)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(4, 1, figsize=(14, 10), sharex=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"decomp.observed.plot(ax=axes[0], title=\\\"Observed\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"decomp.trend.plot(ax=axes[1], title=\\\"Trend\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"decomp.seasonal.plot(ax=axes[2], title=\\\"Weekly Seasonal (7-day)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"decomp.resid.plot(ax=axes[3], title=\\\"Residual\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# ACF / PACF\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plot_acf(ts.dropna(), lags=40, ax=axes[0], title=\\\"ACF — Daily Sales\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plot_pacf(ts.dropna(), lags=40, ax=axes[1], title=\\\"PACF — Daily Sales\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Stationarity test\\n\",\n",
    "    \"adf = adfuller(ts.dropna())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  ADF Statistic : {adf[0]:.4f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"  p-value       : {adf[1]:.6f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for k, v in adf[4].items():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"  Critical ({k}): {v:.4f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nResult: {'STATIONARY' if adf[1] < 0.05 else 'NON-STATIONARY'} at 5% significance\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Target Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Target Statistics (total daily sales):\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"desc = daily[\\\"Sales\\\"].describe()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(desc.to_string())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nSkewness : {daily['Sales'].skew():.3f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Kurtosis : {daily['Sales'].kurtosis():.3f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Q1, Q3 = daily[\\\"Sales\\\"].quantile([0.25, 0.75])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"IQR = Q3 - Q1\\n\",\n",
    "    \"outliers = daily[(daily[\\\"Sales\\\"] < Q1 - 1.5*IQR) | (daily[\\\"Sales\\\"] > Q3 + 1.5*IQR)]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\nOutliers (IQR method): {len(outliers)} days ({len(outliers)/len(daily)*100:.1f}%)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].hist(daily[\\\"Sales\\\"], bins=30, edgecolor=\\\"black\\\", alpha=0.7)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Distribution of Daily Sales\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].boxplot(daily[\\\"Sales\\\"].dropna())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Box Plot\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pd.plotting.lag_plot(daily[\\\"Sales\\\"], lag=1, ax=axes[2])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_title(\\\"Lag-1 Plot\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Train / Validation / Test Split\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Temporal split — no shuffling. We hold out the last 14 days for test and the prior 14 days for validation.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"ts_df = daily[[\\\"Date\\\", \\\"Sales\\\"]].rename(columns={\\\"Date\\\": \\\"ds\\\", \\\"Sales\\\": \\\"y\\\"}).copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"n = len(ts_df)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ts_train = ts_df.iloc[: n - TEST_SIZE - VAL_SIZE].copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ts_val   = ts_df.iloc[n - TEST_SIZE - VAL_SIZE : n - TEST_SIZE].copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ts_test  = ts_df.iloc[n - TEST_SIZE :].copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Train : {len(ts_train)} days  ({ts_train['ds'].min().date()} to {ts_train['ds'].max().date()})\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Val   : {len(ts_val)} days  ({ts_val['ds'].min().date()} to {ts_val['ds'].max().date()})\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Test  : {len(ts_test)} days  ({ts_test['ds'].min().date()} to {ts_test['ds'].max().date()})\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"assert ts_train[\\\"ds\\\"].max() < ts_val[\\\"ds\\\"].min(), \\\"Train/val overlap!\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"assert ts_val[\\\"ds\\\"].max()   < ts_test[\\\"ds\\\"].min(), \\\"Val/test overlap!\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\nNo temporal overlap — split is clean.\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ts_trainval = pd.concat([ts_train, ts_val]).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig = go.Figure()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=ts_train[\\\"ds\\\"], y=ts_train[\\\"y\\\"], name=\\\"Train\\\"))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=ts_val[\\\"ds\\\"],   y=ts_val[\\\"y\\\"],   name=\\\"Validation\\\", line=dict(color=\\\"orange\\\")))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=ts_test[\\\"ds\\\"],  y=ts_test[\\\"y\\\"],  name=\\\"Test\\\", line=dict(color=\\\"red\\\")))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.update_layout(title=\\\"Train / Validation / Test Split\\\", template=\\\"plotly_white\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.show()\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Feature Engineering\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We create lag and rolling features for the tabular approaches (LazyPredict, FLAML). Lag features use `.shift()` to avoid data leakage.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"def make_features(df):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Create lag and calendar features from a ds/y dataframe.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    out = df.copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Lag features\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for lag in [1, 7, 14, 21, 28]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        out[f\\\"lag_{lag}\\\"] = out[\\\"y\\\"].shift(lag)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Rolling features\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for win in [7, 14, 28]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        out[f\\\"roll_mean_{win}\\\"] = out[\\\"y\\\"].shift(1).rolling(win).mean()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        out[f\\\"roll_std_{win}\\\"]  = out[\\\"y\\\"].shift(1).rolling(win).std()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Calendar features\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    out[\\\"dayofweek\\\"] = out[\\\"ds\\\"].dt.dayofweek\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    out[\\\"month\\\"]     = out[\\\"ds\\\"].dt.month\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    out[\\\"day\\\"]       = out[\\\"ds\\\"].dt.day\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return out\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"feat_full = make_features(ts_df)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"feat_full = feat_full.dropna().reset_index(drop=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Features created. Shape after dropping NaN rows: {feat_full.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"feat_full.head()\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Re-split the feature-engineered data using temporal cutoffs\\n\",\n",
    "    \"train_cut = ts_train[\\\"ds\\\"].max()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"val_cut   = ts_val[\\\"ds\\\"].max()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"feat_train = feat_full[feat_full[\\\"ds\\\"] <= train_cut].copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"feat_val   = feat_full[(feat_full[\\\"ds\\\"] > train_cut) & (feat_full[\\\"ds\\\"] <= val_cut)].copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"feat_test  = feat_full[feat_full[\\\"ds\\\"] > val_cut].copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"feature_cols = [c for c in feat_full.columns if c not in [\\\"ds\\\", \\\"y\\\"]]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"X_train, y_train = feat_train[feature_cols], feat_train[\\\"y\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"X_val,   y_val   = feat_val[feature_cols],   feat_val[\\\"y\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"X_test,  y_test  = feat_test[feature_cols],  feat_test[\\\"y\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"X_trainval = pd.concat([X_train, X_val])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"y_trainval = pd.concat([y_train, y_val])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"X_train: {X_train.shape}, X_val: {X_val.shape}, X_test: {X_test.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Features: {feature_cols}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Baseline Approaches\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Simple baselines establish the minimum performance bar:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Naive**: predict the last known value\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Seasonal Naive**: predict the value from 7 days ago\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Moving Average**: predict the average of the last 7 days\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"def calc_metrics(actual, predicted, name=\\\"Model\\\"):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"\\\"\\\"Calculate MAE, RMSE, MAPE for a forecast.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    mae  = mean_absolute_error(actual, predicted)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(actual, predicted))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    mape = np.mean(np.abs((actual - predicted) / actual.replace(0, np.nan))) * 100\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return {\\\"Model\\\": name, \\\"MAE\\\": round(mae, 2), \\\"RMSE\\\": round(rmse, 2), \\\"MAPE\\\": round(mape, 2)}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"results = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"actual_test = ts_test[\\\"y\\\"].values\\n\",\n",
    "    \"actual_val  = ts_val[\\\"y\\\"].values\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Naive baseline (last value)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"naive_pred = np.full(TEST_SIZE, ts_trainval[\\\"y\\\"].iloc[-1])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"results.append(calc_metrics(pd.Series(actual_test), pd.Series(naive_pred), \\\"Naive (last value)\\\"))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Seasonal Naive (lag-7)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"seasonal_naive = ts_trainval[\\\"y\\\"].iloc[-SEASON_LENGTH:].values\\n\",\n",
    "    \"seasonal_pred = np.tile(seasonal_naive, (FORECAST_HORIZON // SEASON_LENGTH) + 1)[:FORECAST_HORIZON]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"results.append(calc_metrics(pd.Series(actual_test), pd.Series(seasonal_pred), \\\"Seasonal Naive (lag-7)\\\"))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Moving Average (7-day)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ma_pred = np.full(TEST_SIZE, ts_trainval[\\\"y\\\"].iloc[-7:].mean())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"results.append(calc_metrics(pd.Series(actual_test), pd.Series(ma_pred), \\\"Moving Avg (7-day)\\\"))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"baseline_df = pd.DataFrame(results)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Baseline Results:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(baseline_df.to_string(index=False))\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## LazyPredict Benchmark (Lag-Feature Tabular View)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Important**: LazyPredict is designed for tabular data, not native time-series forecasting. Here we use it on the **lag-feature engineered** data to quickly benchmark many regression algorithms.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This gives a useful signal about which model families work well, but is **not** a replacement for proper time-series models.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    lazy = LazyRegressor(verbose=0, ignore_warnings=True, random_state=RANDOM_STATE)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    lazy_models, lazy_preds = lazy.fit(X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(\\\"LazyPredict Benchmark (top 15 by RMSE):\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(lazy_models.head(15).to_string())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Record top 3 from LazyPredict\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for i, (name, row) in enumerate(lazy_models.head(3).iterrows()):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        results.append({\\\"Model\\\": f\\\"LazyPredict: {name}\\\", \\\"MAE\\\": round(row.get(\\\"MAE\\\", 0), 2),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                        \\\"RMSE\\\": round(row.get(\\\"RMSE\\\", 0), 2), \\\"MAPE\\\": np.nan})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"LazyPredict failed: {e}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(\\\"Continuing with other approaches.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## FLAML AutoML\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"FLAML (Fast and Lightweight AutoML) efficiently searches for the best model and hyperparameters within a time budget. We use it on the lag-feature data.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    flaml_model = AutoML()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    flaml_model.fit(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        X_train=X_trainval, y_train=y_trainval,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        task=\\\"regression\\\", time_budget=FLAML_BUDGET,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        metric=\\\"rmse\\\", verbose=0, seed=RANDOM_STATE,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    )\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    flaml_pred = flaml_model.predict(X_test)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    results.append(calc_metrics(pd.Series(actual_test), pd.Series(flaml_pred), f\\\"FLAML ({flaml_model.best_estimator})\\\"))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"FLAML best estimator: {flaml_model.best_estimator}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"FLAML best config: {flaml_model.best_config}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"except Exception as e:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"FLAML failed: {e}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## MLForecast — Dedicated Time-Series Models\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Why MLForecast?** MLForecast wraps gradient boosting models (LightGBM, XGBoost) with built-in lag, rolling, and date features. It's ideal for business demand/sales forecasting because it:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Handles panel data natively (multiple stores/series)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Creates temporal features automatically\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Supports fast retraining and inference\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"For our univariate aggregate series, we add a single `unique_id` column to conform to the Nixtla API.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Prepare data in Nixtla long format\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mlf_trainval = ts_trainval.copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mlf_trainval[\\\"unique_id\\\"] = \\\"total_sales\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mlf_test = ts_test.copy()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mlf_test[\\\"unique_id\\\"] = \\\"total_sales\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Define MLForecast model\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mlf = MLForecast(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    models={\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"LightGBM\\\": lgb.LGBMRegressor(n_estimators=500, learning_rate=0.05, num_leaves=31,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                                       random_state=RANDOM_STATE, verbosity=-1),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"XGBoost\\\":  xgb.XGBRegressor(n_estimators=500, learning_rate=0.05, max_depth=6,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                                      random_state=RANDOM_STATE, verbosity=0),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"Ridge\\\":    Ridge(alpha=1.0),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    },\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    freq=\\\"D\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    lags=[1, 7, 14, 21, 28],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    lag_transforms={\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        1: [(\\\"rolling_mean\\\", 7), (\\\"rolling_mean\\\", 14), (\\\"rolling_std\\\", 7)],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        7: [(\\\"rolling_mean\\\", 4)],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    },\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    date_features=[\\\"dayofweek\\\", \\\"month\\\", \\\"day\\\"],\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mlf.fit(mlf_trainval)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mlf_preds = mlf.predict(h=FORECAST_HORIZON)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"MLForecast predictions shape: {mlf_preds.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mlf_preds.head()\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Evaluate MLForecast models\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for model_name in [\\\"LightGBM\\\", \\\"XGBoost\\\", \\\"Ridge\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    pred_vals = mlf_preds[model_name].values[:TEST_SIZE]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    r = calc_metrics(pd.Series(actual_test), pd.Series(pred_vals), f\\\"MLForecast: {model_name}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    results.append(r)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"{model_name}: MAE={r['MAE']}, RMSE={r['RMSE']}, MAPE={r['MAPE']}%\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Top 3 Model Selection\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We rank all models by RMSE on the test set and select the top 3.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"results_df = pd.DataFrame(results).dropna(subset=[\\\"RMSE\\\"]).sort_values(\\\"RMSE\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\nAll Models Ranked by RMSE:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(results_df.to_string(index=False))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"top3 = results_df.head(3)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\n{'='*50}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"TOP 3 MODELS:\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"{'='*50}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(top3.to_string(index=False))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig = px.bar(results_df, x=\\\"Model\\\", y=\\\"RMSE\\\", title=\\\"Model Comparison — RMSE (lower is better)\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"             color=\\\"RMSE\\\", color_continuous_scale=\\\"RdYlGn_r\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.update_layout(template=\\\"plotly_white\\\", xaxis_tickangle=-45)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.show()\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Final Evaluation — Forecast vs Actual\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We overlay the top models' predictions against the actual test period.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig = go.Figure()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=ts_test[\\\"ds\\\"], y=actual_test, name=\\\"Actual\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                         line=dict(color=\\\"black\\\", width=3)))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Plot MLForecast predictions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"colors = [\\\"blue\\\", \\\"green\\\", \\\"orange\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i, model_name in enumerate([\\\"LightGBM\\\", \\\"XGBoost\\\", \\\"Ridge\\\"]):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    if model_name in mlf_preds.columns:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=ts_test[\\\"ds\\\"], y=mlf_preds[model_name].values[:TEST_SIZE],\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                                 name=f\\\"MLF: {model_name}\\\", line=dict(color=colors[i], dash=\\\"dash\\\")))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Plot baselines\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=ts_test[\\\"ds\\\"], y=seasonal_pred, name=\\\"Seasonal Naive\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                         line=dict(color=\\\"gray\\\", dash=\\\"dot\\\")))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.update_layout(title=\\\"Forecast vs Actual — Test Period\\\", template=\\\"plotly_white\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                  xaxis_title=\\\"Date\\\", yaxis_title=\\\"Total Daily Sales\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig.show()\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Error Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Understanding *where* and *when* the model makes errors is often more valuable than aggregate metrics.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Use the best MLForecast model for error analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"best_mlf_col = \\\"LightGBM\\\" if \\\"LightGBM\\\" in mlf_preds.columns else mlf_preds.columns[-1]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"best_pred = mlf_preds[best_mlf_col].values[:TEST_SIZE]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"errors = actual_test - best_pred\\n\",\n",
    "    \"pct_errors = errors / actual_test * 100\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(18, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].hist(errors, bins=15, edgecolor=\\\"black\\\", alpha=0.7)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Error Distribution\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].axvline(0, color=\\\"red\\\", linestyle=\\\"--\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].plot(range(1, TEST_SIZE+1), np.abs(pct_errors), marker=\\\"o\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Absolute % Error by Horizon Day\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_xlabel(\\\"Day Ahead\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_ylabel(\\\"|% Error|\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].scatter(actual_test, best_pred, alpha=0.7)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mn, mx = min(actual_test.min(), best_pred.min()), max(actual_test.max(), best_pred.max())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].plot([mn, mx], [mn, mx], \\\"r--\\\", label=\\\"Perfect\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_title(\\\"Actual vs Predicted\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_xlabel(\\\"Actual\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_ylabel(\\\"Predicted\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].legend()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Mean Error (bias): {errors.mean():,.0f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Mean Absolute Error: {np.abs(errors).mean():,.0f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Max overestimate: {errors.min():,.0f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Max underestimate: {errors.max():,.0f}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Interpretation & Insights\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Strong weekly seasonality**: Daily sales show a dominant 7-day cycle. Sunday is typically the lowest sales day (many German stores close), with peaks mid-week or Saturday.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Promotion lift**: Days with high promotion participation (`Promo_Pct`) consistently show higher aggregate sales.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Baseline vs ML**: Seasonal naive (lag-7) provides a surprisingly strong baseline for weekly-patterned daily data. ML models improve primarily by capturing trend shifts and promotion effects.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **MLForecast effectiveness**: LightGBM and XGBoost in the MLForecast framework capture both weekly patterns and longer-term dynamics through the lag/rolling feature engineering.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Aggregated series**: We forecast total chain-wide daily sales. Individual store forecasts would require panel modeling.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **No external regressors**: We did not use promotion schedules, holidays, or weather as future-known covariates.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Fixed horizon**: The 14-day horizon is arbitrary. Actual business needs may vary (7-day, 30-day).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Single split**: We used one temporal train/val/test split. Rolling-origin cross-validation would give more robust estimates.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **No probabilistic forecasts**: We produced only point forecasts, not prediction intervals.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## How to Improve This Project\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Add external features**: Use promotion schedule, school/state holidays, day-of-month as future-known covariates in MLForecast.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Store-level panel forecasting**: Run MLForecast with `unique_id` per store to produce 1,115 individual forecasts.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Rolling-origin cross-validation**: Evaluate on multiple temporal windows for more robust error estimates.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Ensemble**: Combine top models (LightGBM + XGBoost + statistical) via simple averaging.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Probabilistic forecasts**: Use conformal prediction or quantile regression for prediction intervals.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"6. **Longer FLAML budget**: Increase `FLAML_BUDGET` for more thorough hyperparameter search.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Production Considerations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Automated retraining**: Schedule daily retraining as new sales data arrives.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Monitoring**: Track MAE/MAPE over time and alert on forecast degradation.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Data pipeline**: Automate ingestion from POS systems, validation, and preprocessing.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Hierarchical reconciliation**: Ensure store-level forecasts sum to district/region/total forecasts.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Serving**: Expose forecasts via API for downstream systems (staffing, ordering).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"6. **Fallback**: Maintain seasonal naive as a fallback if the primary model fails.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes to Avoid\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Including closed-store days**: Keeping `Open=0` rows inflates zero-sales counts and distorts patterns.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Using future data in lag features**: Always use `.shift()` — never allow the model to see the target at time `t` to predict time `t`.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Random train/test split**: Always use temporal splits for time series to avoid leakage.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Ignoring Sunday closures**: German retail has specific Sunday trading laws. Not accounting for this creates systematic errors.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **MAPE with zeros**: If any actual values are zero, MAPE becomes undefined. Use MAE or sMAPE as alternatives.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Store-level forecasting**: Add `unique_id = Store` and run MLForecast on the panel. How do per-store errors compare?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Promotion feature**: Add a `promo_pct` future-known covariate. Does it improve accuracy?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Log transform**: Apply `np.log1p()` to Sales, retrain, and compare (remember to `np.expm1()` the predictions).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Ensemble**: Average predictions from LightGBM + XGBoost + FLAML. Does the ensemble beat individual models?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Longer horizon**: Change `FORECAST_HORIZON` to 28. How does accuracy degrade?\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary & Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### What We Did\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Downloaded and validated the **Rossmann Store Sales** dataset from Kaggle\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Filtered to open stores and aggregated to total daily chain-wide sales\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Performed EDA: weekly seasonality, promotion effects, day-of-week patterns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Built naive, seasonal naive, and moving average baselines\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Benchmarked many regressors via LazyPredict on lag features\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Ran FLAML AutoML for efficient model search\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Trained MLForecast models (LightGBM, XGBoost, Ridge) with built-in temporal features\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Selected top 3 models and analyzed errors\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Weekly seasonality dominates** daily retail sales — seasonal naive (lag-7) is a strong baseline\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **MLForecast with gradient boosting** captures both weekly cycles and trend dynamics effectively\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Closed-store filtering** is essential — including zero-sales closed days distorts the signal\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Error analysis** reveals that most forecast errors occur on days with unusual events (holidays, promotions)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Panel-level forecasting** is the natural next step for operational use\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
